title: SpaceX to launch OneWeb 17 mission and return booster to LZ-1
summary: SpaceX is set to launch 40 high-speed internet communication satellites to a polar low Earth orbit on the OneWeb 17 mission on Thursday. Launching from Space Launch Complex 40 (SLC-40) at the Cape Canaveral Space Force Station in Florida, the Falcon 9 is scheduled to lift off at 2:13 PM EST (19:13 UTC) and will mark SpaceX’s 16th orbital launch of 2023–a launch every 4.25 days.

title: Watch live: SpaceX launch and landing on tap today at Cape Canaveral
summary: SpaceX is set to launch a Falcon 9 rocket from Cape Canaveral Space Force Station Thursday with 40 more internet satellites for rival OneWeb, followed eight minutes later by the landing of the rocket’s first stage booster back at the Florida spaceport. Liftoff of the Falcon 9 rocket is set for 2:13 p.m. EST (1913 GMT).

title: Coverage Set as NASA’s SpaceX Crew-5 Prepares to Splashdown
summary: NASA will provide coverage of the agency’s SpaceX Crew-5 mission return to Earth from the International Space Station, beginning with undocking coverage live at 12 a.m. EST on Saturday, March 11. The SpaceX Dragon spacecraft is scheduled to undock from the space station at 2:05 a.m., to begin the journey home.

title: Japanese lunar lander company ispace to go public
summary: Japanese lunar exploration company ispace plans to list its shares on the Tokyo Stock Exchange next month, just before the company attempts its first landing on the moon.

title: Relativity Space scrubs first Terran 1 launch attempt
summary: Relativity Space will wait at least three days before making its next attempt to launch its Terran 1 rocket after propellant temperature issues scrubbed its first launch attempt March 8.

title: U.S. intelligence report: China’s commercial space sector to become global competitor by 2030
summary: The fast growth of China’s commercial space industry is helping the country progress toward its goal of edging out the United States in space, the U.S. intelligence community said in a report released March 8.

title: NASA Sets Coverage for Annual Address, Budget Media Call in March
summary: Administrator Bill Nelson will broadcast his annual State of NASA remarks at 3 p.m. EST on Thursday, March 9. The event will air on NASA Television, the NASA app, and the agency’s website.

title: Relativity Space Scrubs Maiden Flight Of Terran 1 Rocket
summary: On 8th March 2023, Relativity Space scrubbed the Good Luck Have Fun (GLHF) launch due to exceeding launch commit criteria levels for the thermal conditions of Stage 2.

title: NASA, Smithsonian to Discuss Air Quality Satellite Instrument
summary: Media are invited to a joint briefing with NASA and The Smithsonian Astrophysical Observatory at 9 a.m. EDT Tuesday, March 14, to discuss the first space-based instrument to observe major air pollutants across North America every hour during the daytime.

title: Relativity postpones first launch attempt of 3D-printed rocket Terran 1
summary: 3D-printing specialist Relativity Space postponed its first launch attempt on Wednesday, a mission that marks the most significant test yet of the company’s ambitious manufacturing approach.
